<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <title>Go Tournament</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="../assets/style.css">
    </head>

    <body>
    <%- include ('partials/header.ejs')%>
    <%- include ('partials/nav.ejs')%>

    <main>
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Mentor Connections</h2>
            <p>Mentor connections are generally with a player 4 ranks above you or more.</p>
            <div class="inner">
                <header>
                    <h3><a href="/match/<%= data.matchData[0].id %>"><%= data.matchData[0].player0 %></a></h3>
                    <p>A Chimera Ant that is destined to take over the world.</p>
                </header>
                <p>Rank: <%= data.matchData[0].player0Rank %></p>
                <p>Age: 3 months old</p>
            </div>
            <div class="inner">
                <header>
                    <h3><a href="/match/<%= data.matchData[0].id %>"><%= data.matchData[0].player1 %></a></h3>
                    <p>A blind girl who is dang good at this game.</p>
                </header>
                <p>Rank: <%= data.matchData[0].player1Rank %></p>
                <p>Age: 19 years old</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="container">
            <h2>Player Connections</h2>
            <p>Player connections are generally with a player 3 ranks above you or less.</p>
            <div class="inner">
                <header>
                    <h3><a href="/match/<%= data.matchData[0].id %>"><%= data.matchData[1].player0 %></a></h3>
                    <p>Brad is the coolest kid around, next to Chad</p>
                </header>
                <p>Rank: <%= data.matchData[1].player0Rank %></p>
                <p>Age: 22 years old</p>
            </div>
            <div class="inner">
                <header>
                    <h3><a href="/match/<%= data.matchData[0].id %>"><%= data.matchData[1].player1 %></a></h3>
                    <p>Chad is the coolest kid around, next to Brad</p>
                </header>
                <p>Rank: <%= data.matchData[1].player1Rank %></p>
                <p>Age: 22 years old</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <div class="aside">
        <h2>Rankings: Explained</h2>
        <p>Rankings in Go start at a Kyu level for beginners, then progress into amateur Dan,
            and finally professional Dan.  <br><br>Kyu begins at 30 kyu (also denoted as 30k) for absolute beginners
            and goes up to 1 kyu (1k). Once a player reaches the rank of Dan, however,
            they begin at 1 amateur dan (1d), and progress to 7 dan (7d). If a player is fortunate enough to
            progress into the professional ranking, they begin as a 1 professional dan (1p) and the only very best
            can progress to a 9 dan (9p).<br><br>

            Beginner: 30k-20k<br>
            Casual Player: 19k-10k<br>
            Intermediate Amateur: 9k-1k<br>
            Advanced Amateur: 1d-7d<br>
            Professional Player: 1-9p<br>
        </p>
    </div>

    <%- include ('partials/footer.ejs')%>
    </body>
</html>